This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with parsing natural language sentences using Combinatory Categorial Grammar (CCG) parser. It also involves logical reasoning and Recognizing Textual Entailment (RTE), which are common topics in computational linguistics. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing a method to improve the performance of logic-based systems. 

The sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also likely as the paper proposes a method that involves modeling with Markov Random Fields (MRF), which is a common technique in machine learning. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with processing and analyzing natural language text. 

Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms, but these techniques could potentially be used in conjunction with the proposed method.
